                                         JOHANNESBURG - The Johannesburg Metro Police Department has condemned the killing of one of its officers allegedly by a drunk driver. It’s understood the officers were conducting roadside check operations in Soweto on Friday when the driver lost control of his vehicle crashing into Zanele Nelane and another car. The suspect was transported to a nearby hospital where he's in a serious condition. JMPD's Wayne Minaar said, “He’s in a serious condition in hospital but as soon as he’s discharged he will face charges of reckless driving and culpable homicide.”